<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1499950-do-people-find-it-offensive-that-he">Do people find it offensive that he darkened his skin that way?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1499950'><a id="like_count_community_question_1499950" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1499950?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">3 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F42603.Black_Like_Me">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1499950-do-people-find-it-offensive-that-he">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1499950-do-people-find-it-offensive-that-he">See all 6 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/5281527-bridget"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1627105739i/5281527._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/5281527-bridget">Bridget</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">No. Not at all. He did it to see what we as black people dealt with during that time. It&apos;s not like he was doing black face to be a racist butt hole. <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">No. Not at all. He did it to see what we as black people dealt with during that time. It's not like he was doing black face to be a racist butt hole. Because I personally understand why he did it, it doesn't bother me at all. Have you read the book? He gives explanation as to why he was doing it. They may have then, even some now, but many with some level of common sense and critical thinking would understand it, especially once they have read the book.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link834190" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=834190&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F1499950-do-people-find-it-offensive-that-he%2Fanswers%2F834190-no-not-at-all-he-did">flag</a>
</div>
