<div id="review_1803642250" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1803642250" />
    <a title="Benjamin Farr" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49287072-benjamin-farr"><img alt="Benjamin Farr" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1613988571p2/49287072.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1803642250?book_show_action=true">Nov 19, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Benjamin Farr" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Benjamin Farr" href="/user/show/49287072-benjamin-farr">Benjamin Farr</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49287072-benjamin-farr?shelf=2016">2016</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1803642250" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13019784990105967289">The very audacity that a white person&apos;s voice is stronger and louder than the collective suffering of the underclass makes this a discomforting read. What annoys me most about this book is that there are many authentic &apos;Black&apos; voices that have been silenced throughout the years, yet this poorly written book is one that is held up as a beacon of what repression, racism and discrimination feels like - a phenomenon that basically says that unless you are white and experience suffering, then your ac</span>
  <span id="freeText13019784990105967289" style="display:none">The very audacity that a white person's voice is stronger and louder than the collective suffering of the underclass makes this a discomforting read. What annoys me most about this book is that there are many authentic 'Black' voices that have been silenced throughout the years, yet this poorly written book is one that is held up as a beacon of what repression, racism and discrimination feels like - a phenomenon that basically says that unless you are white and experience suffering, then your account is somehow diminished or of lesser value. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13019784990105967289" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
