<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer5999555852531496021">John Howard Griffin was a white American journalist who is best known for his account, <i>Black Like Me</i>, in which he details the experience of darkening his skin and traveling as a black man through through Louisiana, Mississippi, Alabama, and Georgia in 1959. (The racism that he encountered was so disturbing that he cut short the time that he had allotted for this very unique experiment, clearly dem</span>
  <span id="freeText5999555852531496021" style="display:none">John Howard Griffin was a white American journalist who is best known for his account, <i>Black Like Me</i>, in which he details the experience of darkening his skin and traveling as a black man through through Louisiana, Mississippi, Alabama, and Georgia in 1959. (The racism that he encountered was so disturbing that he cut short the time that he had allotted for this very unique experiment, clearly demonstrating that no one would tolerate being treated as many blacks are, if he or she could possibly avoid it.)<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="5999555852531496021" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
</div>

